# ASCII-only output

- Use ASCII characters only in generated code, comments, strings, and documentation.
- Do not introduce Unicode punctuation or symbols (for example: en/em dashes, smart quotes, ellipsis, non-breaking spaces, bullets, emoji).
- Prefer plain ASCII replacements:
  - `-` instead of `–` or `—`
  - `'` and `"` instead of smart quotes
  - `...` instead of `…`
- If editing files that already contain Unicode, avoid adding new Unicode unless explicitly requested or required by an external spec/fixture.
- Before finalizing edits, replace accidental non-ASCII characters in changed text.
